==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*sokjanan'', from Indo-European ''*sag-'' ‘track down’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[seka|sēka]], Old Saxon [[sokian]] (Dutch [[zoeken]]), Old High German [[suohhan]] (German [[suchen]]), Old Norse [[sœkja]] (Swedish [[söka]]), Gothic [[𐍃𐍉𐌺𐌾𐌰𐌽]]; and with Latin [[sagire]] ‘sense by smell’, Old Irish [[saigim]] ‘seek’.

